See themes directory for samples.

How a theme works? Easy. Files (e.g. views, CSS, JavaScript, images) you put in
the active theme directory will overwrite files at other places.

To create a theme, you must be familliar with at least Rails, HAML (for views),
SASS (for CSS).

== Loading and effective order

Just create .sass files and they will be automatically loaded in alphanumeric
order. Remember to prefix them with your module name to avoid naming conflict.

File loading order: modules_core -> modules -> theme

CSS effective order: theme -> modules -> modules_core

